According to the official figures released on Sunday night, 10,408 people have died in SA as a result of the coronavirus. While more than  10 000 deaths is already a significant number, funeral parlours  have  reported a spike in the funerals they are being required to cater for. They report numbers which are much higher than the official reported death toll. So what are we dealing with? Our reporter Graeme Hosken spent the week combing through the death-toll figures with SA’s undertakers. Here is what he found out: This short podcast series follows Sunday Times reporter Alex Patrick and senior reporter Graeme Hosken as they track, record and reflect on the real events and people that make up SA’s biggest Covid-19 news stories. Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Spotify | Player.fm | Pocket Casts.